##
Write a  program to find the Hailstone Sequence of a given number up to 1.
Example: Input any number (positive) to start for Hailstone Sequence : 13
The hailstone sequence starting at 13 is : 13  40  20  10  5  16  8  4  2 1
formula: 3n + 1 or n/2
##
start(){
	piece of input = topiece(bill("Input any number (positive) to start for Hailstone Sequence: ")+take());
    check(input <= 0 ) {serve "Invalid Input";}
    instead {
    	bill("The hailstone sequence starting at "+tochars(input)+" is :");
        repeat(input != 1){
        	bill(" "+tochars(input));
            check(input%2 == 1){input = 3*input + 1;}
            instead {input/=2;}
        }   
        bill(" "+tochars(input));
    }
}
--end
13
--end
Input any number (positive) to start for Hailstone Sequence: 13
The hailstone sequence starting at 13 is : 13 40 20 10 5 16 8 4 2 1